{{Infobox publisher | name = Mileševa printing house | image = [[File:Mileseva Monastery 2.JPG|200px]] | caption = Exterior of the monastery | parent = | status = defunct (1557) | traded_as = | predecessor = | founded = 1544 | founder = | successor = | country = [[Ottoman Empire]] | headquarters = [[Mileševa monastery]] | distribution = | keypeople = [[Hieromonk Mardarije]], Hegumen Danilo | publications = [[srbulje]] | topics = | genre = | imprints = | revenue = | owner = | numemployees = | url = }} The '''Mileševa printing house''' ({{lang-sr|Милешевска штампарија}}) was a printing house established in 1544 in the [[Mileševa monastery]] near [[Prijepolje]], [[Ottoman Empire]] (modern day [[Serbia]]). Three [[srbulje]] books were printed in this printing house. Two in 1544 and 1545 and one in 1557.
== Background == Activities connected with printing in Mileševa began when in 1518 or at the beginning of 1519 when Teodor Ljubavić, who was a [[hieromonk]] of Mileševa, travelled to [[Venice]] to learn printing skills. Ljubavić worked at [[Goražde printing house]] between 1521 and 1523. Between 1533 and 1535 [[Božidar Vuković]] visited Mileševa and concluded an agreement with Mileševa to distribute his books.<ref>{{cite book|title=Recherches sur l'art|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NqGfAAAAMAAJ|year=1991|publisher=Matica|page=206}}</ref>
== Establishing == In 1543 Todor Ljubojević, a monk in Mileševa and son of Božidar, was sent to Venice to join his brother Đurađ and to buy a printing press for the monastery. He was accompanied by Mileševa monk Sava and by [[Hegumen Mardarije|Mardarije]] who was a [[hegumen]] of the [[Banja Monastery]] near [[Priboj]]. At that time Banja Monastery was a seat of the [[metropolitan bishop]] while Mileševa was the richest monastery of Dabar eparchy. That is why those two monasteries were given the task to finance and organize establishing of the printing house in Mileševa and why Mardarije travelled to Venice together with monks from Mileševa.<ref name="Biblioteka1994">{{cite book|last=Biblioteka|first=Matica srpska (Novi Sad, Serbia).|title=Godïsnjak Biblioteke Matice srpske|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0i9JAQAAIAAJ|year=1994|page=29}}</ref>
== Printing == Mileševa printing house was operational in period 1544—1557.<ref name="AćimovićĐorđević1987">{{cite book|last1=Aćimović|first1=Dragoljub|last2=Đorđević|first2=Milivoje|title=Štamparstvo u Užičkom kraju, 1537-1987: povodom 450 godina Rujanske štamparije|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=LRXhAAAAMAAJ|year=1987|publisher=Dimitrije Tucović|page=277}}</ref> Three books were printed in it, [[Psalter]] (Псалтир, 1544), [[Breviary]] (Требник, 1545) and another Psalter (1557).<ref>{{cite book|title=Ćirilske rukopisne knjige Biblioteke Matice srpske: Psaltir Gavrila Trojičanina iz 1643. godine|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dmPgAAAAMAAJ|year=1992|publisher=Biblioteka Matice srpske|page=8<!-- |quote=Псалтир с последовањем (Милешева 1544), Псалтир са синаксаром, часловцем и неким канонима (Милешева 1557... -->}}</ref><ref name="ŠafárikBoškov1963">{{cite book|last1=Šafárik|first1=Pavel Jozef|authorlink1=Pavel Jozef Šafárik|last2=Boškov|first2=Živojin|title=P.J. Šafarik, 1795-1861: zbornik članaka povodom 100-godišnjice smrti|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XIBCAQAAIAAJ|year=1963|publisher=Matica srpska|page=51}}</ref> Psalter of 1544 was edited and prepared by Mardarije and Teodor Ljubavić, based on 1519-20 Psalter of [[Božidar Vuković]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Biblioteka|first=Matica Srpska (Novi Sad)|title=Godǐsnjak Biblioteke Matice srpske za ...|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=prXjAAAAMAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Biblioteka Matice srpske|page=30<!-- |quote=Јеромонаси Мардарије и Теодор приредили су Псалтир 1544. у Милешеви држећи се у свему Псалтира Божидара Вуковића из 1519-20 -->}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Bibliotekar|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dr8qAQAAIAAJ|publisher=Društvo bibliotekara N.R. Srbije|page=1220|quote=...Псалтир из 1544. и Молитвеник из 1545. штампани у Милешеви,...}}</ref>
Psalter was edited and prepared by Mardarije and Teodor Ljubavić, based on 1519-20 Psalter of [[Božidar Vuković]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Biblioteka|first=Matica Srpska (Novi Sad)|title=Godǐsnjak Biblioteke Matice srpske za ...|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=prXjAAAAMAAJ|year=1995|publisher=Biblioteka Matice srpske|page=30<!-- |quote=Јеромонаси Мардарије и Теодор приредили су Псалтир 1544. у Милешеви држећи се у свему Псалтира Божидара Вуковића из 1519-20 -->}}</ref> Trebnik was printed by deak Damjan and Milan from [[Obna]] (region around river Kolubara).<ref>{{cite book|title=Recherches sur l'art|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=NqGfAAAAMAAJ|year=1991|publisher=Matica|page=206}}</ref>
The third book was printed after a pause of twelve years.<ref name="Subotin-Golubović1999">{{cite book|last=Subotin-Golubović|first=Tatǰana|title=Serbian manuscript tradition from 1557 until the middle of the XVIIth century|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1BQVAQAAIAAJ|year=1999|publisher=Srpska Akademija Nauka i Umetnosti|isbn=978-86-7025-282-0|page=38}}</ref> Because it was printed with different types, some sources say that two printing houses existed in Mileševa, both of them founded by the order of hegumen of Mileševa, Danilo.<ref name="DomljanKrleža.1984">{{cite book|last1=Domljan|first1=Žarko|authorlink1=Žarko Domljan|author2=Jugoslavenski leksikografski zavod "Miroslav Krleža."|author3=Jugoslavenski leksikografski zavod "Miroslav Krleža".|title=Likovna enciklopedija Jugoslavije|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tYufAAAAMAAJ|year=1984|publisher=Zavod|page=293<!-- |quote=DANIL, iguman manastira Mileševe u XVI v. Za njegovo je ime vezano osnivanje dveju štamparija istog manastira, prve u razdoblju 1544 —46, druge 1557. U pogovoru prve štampane knjige (Psaltir, dovršen 30. X 1544) stoji da su po njegovu ... -->}}</ref>
